This course provides knowledge and practical skills to conduct mineral prospecting and exploration works. Together with one of the Estonian exploration company master students have a possibility to participate in mineral exploration project including geological fieldworks, sampling and quality assessments of the samples. Students will learn, how to write exploration report and to calculate mineral reserves and resources.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give knowledge and practical skills to conduct mineral prospecting and exploration.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1.	The student knows geological methods for mineral exploration and prospecting.
2.	The student knows international codes for classification of mineral resources and reserves.
3.	The student knows how to apply differrent exploration and prospecting tehqniques to study different mineral deposits.
4.	The student knows how to document and analyze field work data and how to present geological exploration results.
5.	The student knows how to write geological exploration reports and have practical skilles to compile maps of the mineral reserves and geological cross-sections.
